		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Republic of Bulgaria is a country in Southeast Europe. It is bordered by Romania, Serbia, Greece, Turkey and the Black Sea. Earliest modern day inhabitants of Bulgaria date back 8500 years. Between the 6th and 3rd centuries BC the area was inhabited by many people like the Thracians, Celts and Macedonians. The Romans took over the area in 45 AD and brought stability until its dissolution. In 6th century AD the Bulgars settled in the area forming the First Bulgarian Empire in 681 AD. The First Bulgarian Empire was conquered by
   
the Byzantines in the 11th century, however a successful revolt against the Byzantines led to the formation of the Second Bulgarian Empire. In the 13th century the Second Bulgarian Empire was conquered and ruled by the Ottomans for the next 500 years.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/45f2dfe0d5d7598710d8481f9546c252/tumblr_mtdbv6Vpa61rtv2o1o1_1280.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Battle of Achelous between the Bulgarians and the Byzantines</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				In 1878 after the Russo-Turkish War the Third and current Bulgarian state was formed. After the formation of its new borders, many ethnic Bulgarians were left outside the border which then eventually turned into conflicts with its neighbors. After several wars in the Balkans as well as World Wars I and II, Bulgaria became a communist nation under Soviet Union’s influence. After the fall of the Soviet Union, Bulgaria experienced economic and social unrest. Today Bulgaria is a developing country that is member of the European Union and NATO.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
