				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Geographically Bulgaria occupies the eastern part of the Balkan Peninsula. The topography alternates between the Danube Plain to the Balkan Mountains which run across the country. The Black Sea coast is the lowest land in the country. Climate in Bulgaria changes with the regions. The northern areas experience cold winters with significant snow fall, where as the south of the Balkans experience more milder temperatures in the winter to very hot summers.
			</p>
		</div>
		
