				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Ancient gold from the Varna Necropolis</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Madara Rider is a carving on a sheer cliff 23 meters (75 feet) above ground. It is believed to be carved sometime between 7th-8th centuries BC. The life size carving shows a man on a horse stabbing a lion with a spear, and a dog following behind. Nobody knows what the cultural source of this carving is or who this carving depicts. Regardless of its origin, It was listed in UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1979.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
